<h1 class="title">The Tech Professional's Guide to Accelerated Learning</h1>
<p>
<a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1vEYqlKR6zjq0wOdUdXMj8qLFeV4t-oUw/view">https://drive.google.com/file/d/1vEYqlKR6zjq0wOdUdXMj8qLFeV4t-oUw/view</a>
</p>

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Real learning happens when you actively engange with the material, much better than than rereading or copying.</li>
<li>Strategic Note taking: Active engagement with material
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>Write note in YOUR OWN WORDS</li>
<li>Create links to other notes</li>
<li>Document questions (and try to answer them!) and doubts</li>
<li>Create examples</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Writing things in your own words helps you to spot things you dont fully understand</li>
</ul>

<p>
Avoid taking notes with out processing them
</p>

<p>
Document everything! 
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Decision making process</li>
<li>What you actually did</li>
<li>Problems / Solutions</li>
<li>Resources that helped you</li>
</ul>


